8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 642, L.D. 995, “An Act to Provide
10 Funding for Low-income Electric Ratepayer Assistance”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §3214, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2023, c. 201, §1; c. 230,
13 §2; c. 306, §§2 and 3; and c. 361, §§3 to 5, is further amended by enacting at the end a new
14 last blocked paragraph to read:
15 As used in this subsection, "low-income household" means a household that is eligible for
16 an assistance program administered by the Maine State Housing Authority pursuant to Title
17 30-A, section 4722, subsection 1, paragraph W or a means-tested program administered by
18 the Department of Health and Human Services and that has an income of no more than
19 150% of the federal poverty level, as defined in Title 22, section 3762, subsection 1,
20 paragraph C.'
21 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
22 number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment replaces the definition of "low-income household" in the bill. The
2255 amendment provides that a low-income household for the purposes of needs-based low-
2266 income assistance for electricity customers is a household that is eligible for a low-income
2277 assistance program administered by the Maine State Housing Authority or eligible for a
2288 means-tested program administered by the Department of Health and Human Services and
2299 that has an income of no more than 150% of the federal poverty level.
